# SQL + Scripts + Robot Standards

Apply these rules when editing database DDL, shell scripts, and Robot tests.

- Keep database design intent explicit in comments: reactive model, DB as source
  of truth, and persistent message-queue abstraction.
- Preserve relational coherence when changing schema (FKs, cardinalities,
  indices, and trigger/channel alignment).
- Keep SQL initialization idempotent where possible (`IF EXISTS`,
  deterministic drop/create order).
- In shell scripts, prefer safe defaults and clear startup/cleanup behavior
  (`set -euo pipefail`, bounded waits, predictable logs).

## Integration Testing Expectations

- For cross-process changes, add or update Robot tests under `tests/robot/`.
- Ensure scripts used by tests remain aligned with test parameters and timeouts.
- Keep failure output actionable for CI and local debugging.
